1
00:00:00,870 --> 00:00:02,670
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:02,670 --> 00:00:06,240
Hey, Natsu... Our guild's 
gained a lot of members.

3
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:09,190
There's Lucy... And then 
Gajeel and Juvia, right?

4
00:00:09,190 --> 00:00:11,400
And now Wendy and Carla!

5
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:14,690
Maybe I'm one of those 
"bringers of good luck"?

6
00:00:14,690 --> 00:00:16,370
You mean like a Lucky Cat?

7
00:00:16,370 --> 00:00:17,980
Or a jinx?!

8
00:00:18,300 --> 00:00:19,680
Now look here!

9
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:55,820
There isn't any one that really jumps out...

10
00:01:55,820 --> 00:01:56,910
Welcome back.

11
00:01:56,910 --> 00:01:59,050
Already searching for your next job?

12
00:01:59,610 --> 00:02:02,930
You've pretty much gotten 
used to the work here, Wendy.

13
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:09,070
You say that, but she's only taken 
simple jobs located here in the city!

14
00:02:09,070 --> 00:02:10,610
Hey, Carla!

15
00:02:11,660 --> 00:02:16,310
I think that doing a bunch of small 
jobs to gain experience is important.

16
00:02:16,590 --> 00:02:21,030
But shouldn't you try doin' 
a big job pretty soon?

17
00:02:21,030 --> 00:02:24,120
Yeah. Like a request from a distant town.

18
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:30,450
I want to be able to do big jobs 
soon, and be of help to everyone!

19
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:36,720
Wendy's First Big Job!

20
00:02:38,030 --> 00:02:40,950
Be of help to everyone, eh?

21
00:02:40,950 --> 00:02:42,010
Good luck!

22
00:02:42,010 --> 00:02:46,440
Seeing her so honest and brave hearted... 
Can't help but cheer her on.

23
00:02:46,440 --> 00:02:47,650
I will do my best!

24
00:02:47,650 --> 00:02:50,390
You should learn from her example, Lucy.

25
00:02:50,390 --> 00:02:52,900
I'm honest and brave hearted too, you know!

26
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:55,110
Huh? Like, how?

27
00:02:55,110 --> 00:02:57,000
I'm totally honest and brave!

28
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,260
My entire body is concentrated 
honesty and bravery!

29
00:03:00,260 --> 00:03:01,330
Honest?

30
00:03:01,330 --> 00:03:02,880
Brave?

31
00:03:04,290 --> 00:03:06,140
Why, you...

32
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:09,500
But I bet that the ones out 
aways will be surprised

33
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:13,230
there's such a little girl 
here when they get back.

34
00:03:13,230 --> 00:03:15,170
No kidding... Like Gildarts.

35
00:03:16,380 --> 00:03:18,430
Gildarts, huh?

36
00:03:18,430 --> 00:03:21,430
Haven't heard a peep about him, as usual.

37
00:03:21,890 --> 00:03:24,050
How many years has it been 
since he went on that job?

38
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:27,300
Three years... I think?

39
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:28,990
There's no need to worry.

40
00:03:28,990 --> 00:03:32,790
This isn't someone like us we're talking 
about... It's Gildarts, you know?

41
00:03:32,790 --> 00:03:35,750
Yeah, definitely. He's 
in a league of his own.

42
00:03:37,790 --> 00:03:41,060
Now that you mention it, I 
have a perfect job for you.

43
00:03:41,590 --> 00:03:45,170
It says they're searching for a 
wizard that can heal the spirit...

44
00:03:45,170 --> 00:03:48,300
The reward is only so-so, but 
don't you think it's perfect?

45
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:52,680
Let's see here... The town of Onibus?

46
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:54,260
What kind of request is it?

47
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:55,520
Um...

48
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:57,940
"Thank you very much"?

49
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:00,420
So <i>that's</i> where this is going?

50
00:04:01,690 --> 00:04:05,330
I remember! It's all coming back to me now!

51
00:04:05,330 --> 00:04:10,180
The play's actors have all run away, and the 
performances have been a series of failures...

52
00:04:10,180 --> 00:04:14,990
My spirit and body are completely 
worn out. Please make me feel better!

53
00:04:14,990 --> 00:04:16,930
Thank you very much.

54
00:04:16,930 --> 00:04:18,070
Rabian.

55
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:20,260
Rabian? Who's that again?

56
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:22,810
He's the head of that 
Scheherazade drama troupe!

57
00:04:22,810 --> 00:04:25,410
Remember the play we put on before?

58
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:29,280
Frederick and Yanderica!

59
00:04:29,940 --> 00:04:32,870
Wendy... I don't mean this in 
a bad way, but don't do it.

60
00:04:32,870 --> 00:04:36,540
He works you to the bone!

61
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:42,590
It was low pay, and serious labor! 
Plus, we couldn't even go home!

62
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:47,750
I'm also against it. You don't 
have to do that kind of job...

63
00:04:47,750 --> 00:04:49,660
Plus, I have a bad feeling about this.

64
00:04:49,660 --> 00:04:55,100
Your intuition is usually right, 
Carla, but if I can be of help...

65
00:04:55,350 --> 00:04:57,850
You're good-natured to a fault!

66
00:04:57,850 --> 00:05:03,360
Anyway, you can't handle going to a town you've 
never been to and taking on a big job like this.

67
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:07,740
That's not true! I'm going to 
answer this request, you'll see!

68
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:10,090
Fine then, suit yourself.

69
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:12,650
I'm not coming with you.

70
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:16,830
Hey, hold it. Why are you two fighting?

71
00:05:16,830 --> 00:05:20,080
Do you really need to be so 
prickly all the time, Carla?

72
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:28,200
I will take on this job!

73
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:31,980
Wait a minute. You're not planning 
on going alone, are you?

74
00:05:31,980 --> 00:05:35,050
Yes! It'll be more good experience.

75
00:05:35,050 --> 00:05:36,560
Hold up there!

76
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:41,200
Wendy, you've only just gotten 
used to how we do things here.

77
00:05:41,420 --> 00:05:44,830
I can't let you go on some 
far-off request alone!

78
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:52,320
Who's been there before?

79
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:54,860
Let me see... Happy!

80
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:56,010
Me?

81
00:05:59,420 --> 00:06:00,900
And... Freed!

82
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:03,610
You look like you're free. Go with her.

83
00:06:03,610 --> 00:06:05,800
If that is your order, Master...

84
00:06:07,170 --> 00:06:09,550
Why Freed?!

85
00:06:14,630 --> 00:06:16,770
Okay, I'm heading out now!

86
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,480
Be careful, seriously.

87
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:27,360
Freed, make sure to protect Wendy, got it?

88
00:06:27,610 --> 00:06:30,660
You needn't worry. Leave everything to me.

89
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:34,110
Don't do anything unless needed.

90
00:06:34,110 --> 00:06:36,940
This is for Wendy's education, after all.

91
00:06:36,940 --> 00:06:39,100
Aye, sir...

92
00:06:47,140 --> 00:06:49,620
Will she really be okay?

93
00:06:49,620 --> 00:06:53,590
Since Freed's with her, there shouldn't 
be anything to worry about, but...

94
00:06:54,060 --> 00:07:00,770
But he's oddly inflexible about things... 
He does things his own way, you know?

95
00:07:03,980 --> 00:07:08,490
The train to Onibus is not 
running due to a breakdown!

96
00:07:09,150 --> 00:07:13,030
Let me repeat: The train 
to Onibus is not running!

97
00:07:13,030 --> 00:07:15,140
Looks like you get a challenge 
right off the bat.

98
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:17,610
What'll you do, Wendy?

99
00:07:17,610 --> 00:07:23,230
I can fly, see... How about I fly you there?

100
00:07:23,670 --> 00:07:28,840
No... I want to do this job 
as much as I can myself.

101
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:33,340
So... I'm thinking about walking to Onibus!

102
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:37,290
That's gonna take a really long time!

103
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:39,260
Freed, stop her!

104
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:41,980
It is as you say.

105
00:07:41,980 --> 00:07:44,880
See what Freed said?

106
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:46,410
I will also walk.

107
00:07:48,980 --> 00:07:52,640
I will respect Wendy's wishes for this job.

108
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:56,600
It is what the Master said, 
and therefore a rule.

109
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,770
I must obey the rules.

110
00:07:58,770 --> 00:08:01,500
Thank you very much, Freed-san!

111
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:04,920
He's so thick-headed!

112
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:10,890
We're <i>really</i> gonna walk this far?

113
00:08:10,890 --> 00:08:16,180
Speaking more precisely, you will 
not be walking, but flying...

114
00:08:16,180 --> 00:08:18,300
It doesn't matter much one way or the other!

115
00:08:18,550 --> 00:08:21,080
Words should be used correctly.

116
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:25,230
For a rune-user like myself, I know 
well the importance of proper language.

117
00:08:25,230 --> 00:08:28,190
Yeah, that's great and all, but...

118
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:31,970
Let's go. If we don't 
hurry, the sun will set.

119
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:40,120
What?! There's another request 
from that drama troupe?

120
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:46,020
Yeah... I wanted to go with her, 
but the master stopped me...

121
00:08:53,090 --> 00:08:55,510
Why are you doing vocal exercises?

122
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:58,500
Always be prepared, I say.

123
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:00,200
Prepared for what?

124
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:06,140
I understand what the master is saying... But I 
can't help but worry about just the three of them.

125
00:09:06,140 --> 00:09:07,720
I will go after them!

126
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:09,300
Didn't take her long to get ready...

127
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:12,110
And wait, isn't that even 
more luggage than usual?

128
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:15,050
Of course!

129
00:09:15,860 --> 00:09:17,570
You brought it with you?

130
00:09:17,570 --> 00:09:20,160
I took it instead of my reward.

131
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:22,530
During the tough times, or the sad times,

132
00:09:22,530 --> 00:09:26,640
when I look at this wardrobe and these 
props, I feel better for some reason.

133
00:09:27,340 --> 00:09:32,200
Sometimes I put on the costumes, and 
put on the play again, all by myself!

134
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:34,680
You were really that into it?

135
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:37,970
And I think you're getting 
close to the cliff there...

136
00:09:38,730 --> 00:09:43,220
Oh, no! I heard that the train 
to Onibus isn't running!

137
00:09:44,330 --> 00:09:47,780
I knew it! We should have gone with her.

138
00:09:47,780 --> 00:09:48,650
Lucy!

139
00:09:48,650 --> 00:09:51,520
Right! What about you, Carla?

140
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:54,610
What a pain she is.

141
00:09:54,610 --> 00:09:59,010
She told me I didn't have to come, 
so I should just let her be!

142
00:09:59,010 --> 00:10:03,380
I mean, why did she take that 
job in Onibus to begin with?

143
00:10:03,380 --> 00:10:06,060
It's not like there's any 
benefit to going far off.

144
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:08,890
Honestly, this is such a waste of time.

145
00:10:08,890 --> 00:10:10,690
Total waste of effort!

146
00:10:10,690 --> 00:10:13,340
This isn't just inefficient, it's ludicrous!

147
00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:17,240
...she says, while coming with us.

148
00:10:17,670 --> 00:10:23,270
Knowing Wendy, she's probably not using the 
he-cat or Freed's powers, but walking there.

149
00:10:23,590 --> 00:10:26,030
This is going to be a long trip.

150
00:10:26,030 --> 00:10:29,920
I'm more worried about us three than them...

151
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:33,830
I'm sorry for bringing you into this.

152
00:10:33,830 --> 00:10:36,120
This is for a companion, so don't worry.

153
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,860
Hey, let's rest a little, okay?

154
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:42,360
But it feels like it'll rain, so let's hurry.

155
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:45,310
I can sense the air currents.

156
00:10:45,310 --> 00:10:49,140
No way... With it this sunny out?

157
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:52,640
What's wrong with this weather?

158
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,630
We have to find shelter from the rain!

159
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:59,520
With my power, it would be a 
simple task to deflect the rain.

160
00:10:59,820 --> 00:11:02,760
All I would have to do is cast 
runes where rain couldn't fall.

161
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:07,720
But the rule this time is to avoid 
helping Wendy unless forced to.

162
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:13,670
But then again, if I let Wendy catch a cold, 
what would be the point of me coming at all?

163
00:11:14,730 --> 00:11:18,070
What... What should I do?!

164
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:23,300
Tell me, Laxus!

165
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:27,670
If you were here, what would you do?!

166
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:31,380
Answer me, Laxus!!!

167
00:11:31,380 --> 00:11:33,420
Freed-san!

168
00:11:33,420 --> 00:11:35,050
Over here!

169
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:38,830
Thank goodness.

170
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:42,190
I see that staying my hand 
was the correct decision.

171
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:45,210
What are you muttering about?

172
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:47,820
It is better that you not know.

173
00:11:49,470 --> 00:11:53,440
I wonder what goes on inside Freed's head?

174
00:11:56,920 --> 00:12:00,770
Why do I have to be stuck 
in this cramped space?

175
00:12:00,770 --> 00:12:02,490
...she says.

176
00:12:02,490 --> 00:12:06,780
We don't have any other place to 
get out of the rain, that's why!

177
00:12:06,780 --> 00:12:08,780
...she says.

178
00:12:08,780 --> 00:12:12,660
Ah... I'm worried about the 
costumes and props getting wet...

179
00:12:12,660 --> 00:12:15,080
...she says.

180
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:18,990
What?! Lucy and Erza went after them?

181
00:12:18,990 --> 00:12:20,350
That's right.

182
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:22,870
They couldn't stand it after all.

183
00:12:22,870 --> 00:12:25,630
And what were <i>you</i> doing?

184
00:12:25,630 --> 00:12:26,530
Sleeping.

185
00:12:26,530 --> 00:12:31,100
Righto! I get the picture, 
and I can't stand it either!

186
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:33,360
Natsu!

187
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:37,400
Does he know that the train isn't running?

188
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:41,840
I don't want to ride it!

189
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:45,890
But if I don't, I can't get to Onibus...

190
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:48,610
But I don't wanna ride it!

191
00:12:48,610 --> 00:12:51,620
Make up your mind already!

192
00:12:51,620 --> 00:12:54,140
We can't depart with you like this!

193
00:12:54,140 --> 00:12:58,200
I'll ride! But please, run so 
that it doesn't sway at all!

194
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,920
That's impossible!

195
00:13:03,130 --> 00:13:05,770
Attention, passengers.

196
00:13:05,770 --> 00:13:11,860
Due to a railway accident, this train 
will be returning before reaching Onibus.

197
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:15,140
This train will not stop at Onibus.

198
00:13:15,140 --> 00:13:19,760
It is running between Magnolia 
and prior to Onibus.

199
00:13:27,620 --> 00:13:30,130
I'm sure glad the rain let up.

200
00:13:30,130 --> 00:13:31,910
But it's getting dark.

201
00:13:32,410 --> 00:13:35,000
Looks like we're going to 
have to camp out tonight.

202
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:38,480
We can sleep in that cave,

203
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:40,600
but the problem is food.

204
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:43,710
You could at least help us gather food.

205
00:13:43,950 --> 00:13:46,380
Otherwise, we'll be so hungry we'll faint!

206
00:13:46,380 --> 00:13:47,420
Worry not.

207
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:53,140
I am a man who knows what 
should, and shouldn't, be done.

208
00:13:53,140 --> 00:13:55,890
Everything he says is stiff, stiff, stiff...

209
00:13:55,890 --> 00:14:00,100
I have an idea of what we may do for 
food. I will make preparations shortly.

210
00:14:00,370 --> 00:14:01,770
Really?

211
00:14:01,770 --> 00:14:03,560
That's a member of the Raijinshuu for you!

212
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:06,200
You can count on them when times get tough!

213
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:07,070
Yeah!

214
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:11,210
When you enter these runes...

215
00:14:12,690 --> 00:14:14,620
...Winged Fish will fall!

216
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:16,880
Why winged fish?!

217
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:19,820
This is near the winged 
fish's migration route.

218
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:23,850
Now is the season where flocks 
of winged fish come to lay eggs.

219
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:27,130
Can you eat these?

220
00:14:28,090 --> 00:14:30,440
They're really gross...

221
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:33,930
We tried them before, and paid the price...

222
00:14:33,930 --> 00:14:37,070
Or so you thought, but you were simply naive.

223
00:14:37,070 --> 00:14:39,690
You broiled them, yes?

224
00:14:39,930 --> 00:14:42,650
There is a knack to cooking winged fish.

225
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:52,110
Are you good at cooking, Freed-san?

226
00:14:54,370 --> 00:15:00,790
I wouldn't go that far, but I have cooked on 
occasion while working with Laxus and the Raijinshuu.

227
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:06,900
Looks delicious!

228
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:08,800
The taste will live up to the presentation.

229
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:11,510
Now, eat your fill.

230
00:15:11,510 --> 00:15:13,650
Let's eat!

231
00:15:21,010 --> 00:15:24,920
Yeah, it wasn't a problem 
with how we cook them...

232
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:27,750
I'm pretty sure I saw some 
nuts and berries over there...

233
00:15:27,750 --> 00:15:29,310
Let's eat those.

234
00:15:29,310 --> 00:15:30,260
Aye...

235
00:15:31,450 --> 00:15:33,410
No one likes a picky eater.

236
00:15:34,020 --> 00:15:36,880
A wizard's body is their asset, after all.

237
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:46,910
Wasn't there anything else to eat?

238
00:15:47,370 --> 00:15:49,300
If there was, we'd be eating it...

239
00:15:50,100 --> 00:15:54,080
See? This is why I didn't want to come!

240
00:15:56,570 --> 00:16:01,600
The train between Onibus and 
Magnolia is now arriving.

241
00:16:02,030 --> 00:16:07,060
This train will be departing in 
the direction of Onibus shortly!

242
00:16:07,060 --> 00:16:10,930
Sir, we're going to depart again.

243
00:16:11,340 --> 00:16:15,780
How many times have you gone 
back and forth since yesterday?

244
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:23,020
First the mountains, and now a desert?

245
00:16:23,020 --> 00:16:26,160
Freed-san, you don't mind the heat?

246
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:29,780
I bet he's secretly casting 
some magic to keep cool...

247
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:34,040
I could never think of making things easier 
for myself and ignoring my companions.

248
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:36,160
It's simply a matter of 
controlling one's thoughts.

249
00:16:38,930 --> 00:16:40,270
It's no use...

250
00:16:40,270 --> 00:16:40,850
Happy!

251
00:16:42,180 --> 00:16:45,320
Wait a moment... I'll make you feel better!

252
00:16:45,780 --> 00:16:49,440
Even though using magic will 
lower her own energy...

253
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:54,250
And yet, she doesn't mind! How 
incredibly kind this girl is!

254
00:16:55,070 --> 00:17:00,230
You needn't use your magic. 
I will handle this.

255
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:02,150
What will you do?

256
00:17:07,620 --> 00:17:09,900
First, I lay him down like this.

257
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:14,300
Next, I write the spell.

258
00:17:16,850 --> 00:17:20,810
Anyone inside these runes 
cannot feel the heat!

259
00:17:20,810 --> 00:17:24,680
The rock is so hot, I'm going to burn...

260
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:28,890
It takes some time for the runes to set.

261
00:17:29,380 --> 00:17:33,180
Although it's pointless 
once he leaves the runes...

262
00:17:33,180 --> 00:17:34,440
Aye...

263
00:17:35,710 --> 00:17:38,090
Is this really the right direction?

264
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:40,540
I'm sure this is the right way.

265
00:17:42,370 --> 00:17:42,950
Stay back!

266
00:17:44,290 --> 00:17:45,640
Erza!

267
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:51,630
Just a little more. Keep it up.

268
00:17:53,250 --> 00:17:54,550
A storm is coming!

269
00:17:54,550 --> 00:17:57,760
A storm? You mean a sandstorm?

270
00:17:57,760 --> 00:18:00,890
This area is famous for 
its cursed sandstorms!

271
00:18:01,970 --> 00:18:04,080
We have to hide somewhere!

272
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:06,580
There is nowhere to hide in this desert.

273
00:18:06,580 --> 00:18:07,430
We run!

274
00:18:08,260 --> 00:18:11,230
It's no use... I can't get out!

275
00:18:11,230 --> 00:18:13,360
Can't you do anything?

276
00:18:13,360 --> 00:18:14,230
That's it!

277
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:18,610
Time for punishment, Princess?

278
00:18:18,610 --> 00:18:21,410
Not that! Save Erza!

279
00:18:21,410 --> 00:18:23,080
As you wish.

280
00:18:27,430 --> 00:18:30,090
It is no use. She is too heavy. 
I cannot move her at all.

281
00:18:30,090 --> 00:18:31,210
How rude!

282
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:35,020
Oh, no... The power of 
my Spirits isn't enough?

283
00:18:35,020 --> 00:18:36,920
Lucy-san!

284
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:39,140
Huh? Carla, too?

285
00:18:40,710 --> 00:18:43,050
We were worried, so we came after you.

286
00:18:43,050 --> 00:18:45,250
Looks like those three are fine...

287
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:47,100
Erza, what's wrong?

288
00:18:47,910 --> 00:18:49,300
Well, you see...

289
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:54,670
This is bad. Soon this area will 
be engulfed by the sandstorm.

290
00:18:58,730 --> 00:19:01,460
Don't worry about me! Everyone, go!

291
00:19:01,460 --> 00:19:03,090
What are you saying?

292
00:19:03,090 --> 00:19:08,080
This weight is odd... It is almost 
like a giant clump of metal...

293
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:13,040
Is Erza-san holding onto 
something very heavy, maybe?

294
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:16,270
I'm still holding onto the play's props.

295
00:19:16,980 --> 00:19:19,160
Well, yeah, that's heavy all right!

296
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:22,510
But without these, I can't put on the show!

297
00:19:22,510 --> 00:19:25,300
The job isn't to be temporary 
actors this time anyway!

298
00:19:26,870 --> 00:19:28,180
I'm sorry...

299
00:19:28,830 --> 00:19:31,360
Farewell, my memories...

300
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:36,710
Farewell, my rock, my foundation!

301
00:19:36,710 --> 00:19:38,830
Just dig 'em up later!

302
00:19:38,830 --> 00:19:40,190
Punishment, yes?

303
00:19:44,040 --> 00:19:46,360
There's no time to escape any longer!

304
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:49,470
If we get sucked up in that, it 
will be impossible to get out!

305
00:19:51,070 --> 00:19:53,370
I'll do something about it!

306
00:19:53,370 --> 00:19:54,790
Wendy...

307
00:19:54,790 --> 00:19:58,680
Roar of the Sky Dragon!

308
00:20:07,910 --> 00:20:10,890
The cursed sandstorm has vanished!

309
00:20:10,890 --> 00:20:12,560
You did it!

310
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:15,310
Wendy... Wow!

311
00:20:25,490 --> 00:20:28,370
Hello! Thank you very much.

312
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:32,070
Why is he so happy?

313
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:34,800
I made up with my performers,

314
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:37,730
so we can put on our play now!

315
00:20:37,730 --> 00:20:41,930
And there are plenty of 
customers! Thank you very much.

316
00:20:41,930 --> 00:20:46,840
No... Why did we struggle 
so hard to get here, then?

317
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:50,560
And I went through all the 
trouble of digging them up!

318
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:53,070
I'm beat...

319
00:20:56,600 --> 00:21:02,310
I ate too many winged fish, 
and now I don't feel well.

320
00:21:03,730 --> 00:21:04,650
No!

321
00:21:05,090 --> 00:21:06,690
I can't even stand...

322
00:21:08,220 --> 00:21:10,330
Hey!

323
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:12,070
Natsu-san!

324
00:21:12,070 --> 00:21:16,520
Finally, they fixed the 
tracks and I made it here...

325
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:21,780
But I spent the whole time goin' back 
and forth from Magnolia to Onibus...

326
00:21:22,350 --> 00:21:23,670
I'm...

327
00:21:26,710 --> 00:21:28,340
His attitude's totally different!

328
00:21:28,340 --> 00:21:32,450
Falling asleep here is hurting 
my business! Hey, you!

329
00:21:33,470 --> 00:21:35,930
Get rid of all of them!

330
00:21:36,370 --> 00:21:40,060
It's a big job, so I'll make 
sure to pay you a reward.

331
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:52,780
I can't believe this was my first big job...

332
00:21:53,010 --> 00:22:00,010
Why not? Everyone was worried about you, but 
in the end you were more useful to them.

333
00:22:00,010 --> 00:22:04,510
You've done a good job.  You should be proud.

334
00:22:04,510 --> 00:22:06,300
Really?

335
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:13,260
Yes. I think so.

336
00:22:14,470 --> 00:22:15,680
You're right!

337
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:22,900
Thank you very much!

338
00:23:55,990 --> 00:23:59,450
It's finally here! Fairy 
Tail's traditional road race!

339
00:23:59,450 --> 00:24:03,330
Yeah! This year's finally 
gonna be the year I win!

340
00:24:03,990 --> 00:24:08,480
Natsu, have you forgotten my magic? 
I'll fly straight to the goal!

341
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:11,830
What are you saying? You have 
to run this time, Happy.

342
00:24:11,830 --> 00:24:13,590
What? Me too?

343
00:24:13,590 --> 00:24:17,220
Next: The 24-Hour Endurance Road Race!

344
00:24:17,220 --> 00:24:20,710
But my running speed is so 
much slower than everyone's!

345
00:24:20,710 --> 00:24:22,350
I'm not really suited for 
the physical stuff...

346
00:24:22,350 --> 00:24:23,640
Carla's running, too.

347
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:24,600
I'll do it!

348
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,990


